<subSubSection id="C367655EFF92FFBC6EE2F8C8FAF7F9E3" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="261" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC236D5FF92FFBC6EE2F8C8FAF7F9E3" blockId="15.[151,1437,1893,2028]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="261" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">
This is a large, endemic Chinese species mainly occurring in 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF92FFA36D34F8C8FC4BFE65" box="[833,905,1893,1919]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Fujian</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF92FFA36DCBF8C8FBE7FE65" box="[958,1061,1893,1919]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF92FFA36A5AF8C8FB29FE65" author="Needham, J. G." box="[1071,1259,1893,1919]" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" pagination="227 - 231" refId="ref14437" refString="Needham, J. G. (1930) A manual of the dragonflies of China. Peiping: The Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, 227 - 231." type="book chapter" year="1930">Needham (1930)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide any figures for this species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF92FFA36FBBF824FDB8FEBE" author="Asahina, S." box="[462,634,1929,1956]" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" pagination="204 - 228" refId="ref13416" refString="Asahina, S. (1956) Dragonflies from West Tien-Mu-Shan, Central China. Entomologiske Meddelelser, 27, 204 - 228." type="journal article" year="1956">Asahina (1956)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF92FFA36C86F827FCB8FEB9" authorityName="Asahina" authorityYear="1956" box="[755,890,1930,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suensoni">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF92FFA36C86F827FCB8FEB9" box="[755,890,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">M. suensoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on base of a female specimen from Tianmushan, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF92FFA36EE2F800FF3CFEDD" box="[151,254,1965,1991]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
. After carefully studying another female specimen collected from the 
<typeStatus id="54C68877FF92FFA36A6EF803FB89FED2" box="[1051,1099,1966,1992]" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF92FFA36AA5F803FF20FEF6" authority="Chao (1965)" authorityName="Chao" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suensoni">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF92FFA36AA5F803FA9BFEDD" box="[1232,1369,1966,1991]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">M. suensoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF92FFA36B14F800FF20FEF6" author="Chao, H. - F." pageId="15" pageNumber="260" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
believed it was a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF92FFA36C0AF87FFD23FEF1" authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[639,737,2001,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF92FFA36C0AF87FFD23FEF1" box="[639,737,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="260">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was finally accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF92FFA36A32F87CFAC7FEF6" author="Asahina, S." box="[1095,1285,2001,2028]" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref13502" refString="Asahina, S. (1985 b) Contributions to the taxonomic knowledge of the Megalestes species of continental South Asia (Odonata, Synlestidae). Cho-Cho, 8 (10), 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Asahina (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF92FFA36B65F87CFA5EFEF6" author="Chao, H. - F." box="[1296,1436,2001,2028]" pageId="15" pageNumber="260" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
also doubted one of the 
<typeStatus id="54C68877FF8DFFBC6FEAFF3AFE0DF9AB" box="[415,463,151,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8DFFBC6C17FF3AFD06F9AB" authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[610,708,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8DFFBC6C17FF3AFD06F9AB" box="[610,708,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the teneral male from 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF8DFFBC6DB2FF3AFBE1F9A8" box="[967,1059,151,178]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
) was true of this species. We have explored 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF8DFFBC6E8AFF16FE9BF9CF" box="[255,345,187,213]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
for many years and have never found 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8DFFBC6D76FF16FCA6F9CF" authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[771,868,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8DFFBC6D76FF16FCA6F9CF" box="[771,868,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the similar-sized species 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF8DFFBC6AC7FF16FA87F9CE" authorityName="Chao" authorityYear="1965" box="[1202,1349,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omeiensis">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF8DFFBC6AC7FF16FA87F9CE" box="[1202,1349,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. omeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present. We agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF8DFFBC6F1AFF72FE3EF9E3" author="Chao, H. - F." box="[367,508,222,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
to believe that Needham confused these two species in his original study.
